    "body": "### Problem\n\n(followup to https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37971 @OleksandrChekhovskyi )\n\nWith 'autoread' enabled, the reloaded buffer contents somehow, sometimes, confuses `ftplugin/help.lua`.\n\nIt seems that `query:iter_matches()` calls `get_node_text` and the parser's notion of the buffer-contents differs from the actual buffer contents.\n\nI suppose this won't happen to most users unless they are editing help files (like me).\n\n```\nvim.schedule callback: …/runtime/lua/nvim/autoread.lua:146:\nFileType Autocommands for \"*\"..function <SNR>1_LoadFTPlugin[20]..script …/runtime/ftplugin/help.lua:\nVim(runtime):E5113: Lua chunk: …/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter.lua:216: Index out of bounds\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_buf_get_text'\n\t…/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter.lua:216: in function 'get_node_text'\n\t…/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/query.lua:558: in function 'handler'\n\t…/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/query.lua:843: in function '_match_predicates'\n\t…/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/query.lua:1082: in function '(for generator)'\n\t…/runtime/ftplugin/help.lua:91: in function 'runnables'\n\t…/runtime/ftplugin/help.lua:124: in main chunk\n\t[C]: in function 'checktime'\n\t…/runtime/lua/nvim/autoread.lua:146: in function <…/runtime/lua/nvim/autoread.lua:138>\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'checktime'\n\t…/runtime/lua/nvim/autoread.lua:146: in function <…/runtime/lua/nvim/autoread.lua:138>\n```\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIdeally, root cause the bug, maybe we can signal to `query:iter_matches()` what the updated buffer-contents are.\n\nAlternatively, a hacky fix is to add another `pcall` to: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/145b20eb89c902a6b1755c194a035411381c4a36/runtime/ftplugin/help.lua#L121-L125\n\nBut that means potential bugs in the future will be hidden.",
